replies.body:
For me he's a tank with loads of utility. His chimes do decent base damage and I take him as a tank support since it can be hard to position to land his stun if you can get blown up quickly. His ult is very good for isolating people, catching them out or really any number of things since it's so flexible. Personally I go 0-18-12 for thunderlords. My runes are early ap dueling power since he can be a really lane bully early on with his meeps, with some flat ap quints, flat mr blues, armour seals and either ad marks or magic pen marks.
My build is just straight up as tanky as possible though if I don't have many chimes early on I may switch frozen heart for the frozen gauntlet.
